sections.Biology:
Manticores have an overall body-plan similar to scorpions, but can grow almost as large as a lobster. They possess six legs and larger stinger-tail, which curves up over the body to hang over the head. They have a series of threatening-looking spines on each body segment, running up the sides of the body and tail. They are mostly green in color.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Dohaeris]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Their most recognizable features are the designs on the plates of their bodies, particularly the marking on the final plate of their tails which resembles a human face. Because of this design they are also sometimes referred to as the &quot;Death's Head Manticore&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Manticore venom is extremely lethal, and even a single sting is usually more than enough to kill a person. Extracted manticore venom is one of the most potent [[Poison|poisons]] which are used by the world's assassins, sometimes by coating bladed weapons with it, so that even a single scratch will kill.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

