=== [[Season 4]] ===

[[Grand Maester]] [[Pycelle]] and [[Qyburn]] assess that [[Oberyn Martell]] coated his spear with manticore venom prior to his duel with Ser [[Gregor Clegane]]. While Gregor won the duel by crushing Oberyn's head in, the poisoned wounds he took left him in agony, and he is now comatose. The effects of the poison are horrific, making the flesh around Gregor's wounds putrefy, which produces an overpowering stench. Pycelle regretfully tells Queen [[Cersei Lannister]] that Ser Gregor is beyond any hope of healing, but Qyburn insists that he can use the knowledge he has gained from unethical human experimentation to save Gregor's life. Cersei gives him permission to proceed, though he warns that the process will &quot;change&quot; Gregor.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
